{"lemma":"شَبُّ","slug":"شَبُّ","root":"ش.ب.ب","root_slug":"ش-ب-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ب-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":10},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n21521","n21525","n21526"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8F%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to become a young adult, to grow up"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be brisk, to be lively, to be sprightly"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to raise one's head (as when trying to reach or look at something), to stand on the tiptoes, to stretch up","examples":[{"text":"كان هناك ولد صغير يتكلّم ويحاول أن يشبّ على أصابعه لينظر من النافذة.","english":"There was a small boy talking and trying to rear on his toes to look through the window."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to raise the forelegs, to prance"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to kindle, to inflame, to ignite (also figuratively, such as of war kindled)","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to kindle, to inflame, to ignite (also figuratively, such as of war kindled); to break out","tags":["intransitive","transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to raise, to lift; to heighten; to highlight, to intensify (also figuratively, and particularly if done with colours or when referring to physical qualities and attributes, such as beauty and attractiveness)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of شَبَّ (šabba, “to raise; to kindle”) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"vitriol","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"alum","tags":["collective"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʃab.ba/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n21521","headword_ar":"شَبَّ","root":"$b","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$abaAbN","text_ar":"شَبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K *) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$abiybapN","text_ar":"شَبِيبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K *) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ubuwbN","text_ar":"شُبُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$abiybN","text_ar":"شَبِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He became a youth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"young man;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he attained to the state termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$abaAbN","text_ar":"شَبَابٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"meaning as expl. below;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K;) said of a boy. (S, Msb.) [And in like manner"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ab~ato","text_ar":"شَبَّتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said of a girl, i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She became a young woman."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ub~a","text_ar":"شُبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"used as a noun: see below. ―         -b3-  [Perhaps as an inf. n. of which the verb is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ab~a","text_ar":"شَبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (as Freytag has assumed,) but more probably of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ub~a","text_ar":"شُبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which will be found mentioned in this paragraph, for I do not find the former verb in the requisite sense,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ab~N","text_ar":"شَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies Anything's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"becoming, raised,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"elevated."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ab~a","text_ar":"شَبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a horse, (S, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ibaAbN","text_ar":"شِبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$abiybN","text_ar":"شَبِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ubuwbN","text_ar":"شُبُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was brisk, lively,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sprightly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K, *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and raised his fore legs"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"together,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as though in leaping,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and played."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ab~at","text_ar":"شَبَّت"},{"kind":"text","text":"in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$bw","text_ar":"شبو"},{"kind":"text","text":", said of a mare.]) And likewise"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, restive,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"refractory:"},{"kind":"text","text":"one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"briy^otu A_ilayoka mino $ibaAbihi","text_ar":"برِيْتُ اـِلَيْكَ مِنْ شِبَابِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$abiybihi","text_ar":"شَبِيبِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiDaADihi","text_ar":"عِضَاضِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDiyDihi","text_ar":"عَضِيضِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I am irresponsible to thee for his being restive,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"refractory,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and for"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his biting"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ab~ati Aln~aAru","text_ar":"شَبَّتِ النَّارُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [aor., accord. to rule,"},{"kind":"text","text":",] (Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ub~at","text_ar":"شُبَّت"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pass. of the trans. verb"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ab~a","text_ar":"شَبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v. infrà], inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ubuwbN","text_ar":"شُبُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(which is of the intrans., TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ab~N","text_ar":"شَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(which is of the trans. verb, TA),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The fire burned, burned up, burned brightly"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fiercely, blazed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flamed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K. [See also 5.]) [And hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ab~ati AlHarobu bayonahumo","text_ar":"شَبَّتِ الحَرْبُ بَيْنَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"War,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the war, burned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"burned fiercely, between them"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ub~a","text_ar":"شُبَّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was raised,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"elevated."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ab~a Aln~aAru","text_ar":"شَبَّ النَّارُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ab~N","text_ar":"شَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ubuwbN","text_ar":"شُبُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) or the latter is the inf. n. of the intrans. verb mentioned above, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He kindled the fire;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made it to burn, burn up, burn brightly"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fiercely, blaze,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flame;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K; *) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$b~bhA","text_ar":"شبّبها","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ta$obiybN","text_ar":"تَشْبِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (L;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A$b~hA","text_ar":"اشبّها","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A and TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"H$","text_ar":"حش"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$abaAhaA","text_ar":"شَبَاهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$bw","text_ar":"شبو"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ab~a AlHaroba","text_ar":"شَبَّ الحَرْبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He kindled war,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the war;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made it to burn,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"burn fiercely."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b3-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ab~a","text_ar":"شَبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", said of the blackness of a garment, (Sh, A, TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It heightened and increased,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made to appear bright and beautiful, and"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as it were"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"burning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"glowing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh, TA,) the whiteness of the wearer. (Sh, A, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ab~a lawonahaA","text_ar":"شَبَّ لَوْنَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(aor. as above, S) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1493},{"kind":"text","text":"(a woman's hair)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"showed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"set off,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and rendered beautiful, her colour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"complexion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a woman's head-covering, and her hair,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"increased, and showed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heightened, and set off,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"her beauty:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a woman's black headcovering)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"increased her fairness, and rendered her beautiful."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ya$ub~u Alwajoha","text_ar":"يَشُبُّ الوَجْهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", said of patience, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It gives beauty and colour to the countenance."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA, from a trad.) ―         -b4-  See also 4, in two places."}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","Msb","K","TA","O","Sh","A"]},{"entry_id":"n21525","headword_ar":"شَبٌّ","root":"$b","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", and its fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ab~apN","text_ar":"شَبَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAb~N","text_ar":"شَابٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stones of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaAj","text_ar":"زَاج"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vitriol"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stones from which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zAj","text_ar":"زاج"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the like thereof are obtained; the best whereof is that which is brought from El-Yemen, which is white"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$b~","text_ar":"شبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and is very glistening:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ab~N yamaAniY~N","text_ar":"شَبٌّ يَمَانِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ab~N","text_ar":"شَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"alone, is a name now commonly given to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"alum:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] or it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain thing resembling"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zAj","text_ar":"زاج"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a species thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to El-Fárábee, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stones from which come"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zAj","text_ar":"زاج"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"Az says, it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of the minerals produced by God in the earth, with which one tans, and resembling"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zAj","text_ar":"زاج"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the name [correctly] heard is thus, with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":", but is by some mistranscribed with the three-dotted"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"v","text_ar":"ث"},{"kind":"text","text":", [i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$av~N","text_ar":"شَثٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] which is a kind of tree of bitter taste, and I know not whether one tans with it or not: accord. to Mtr, in the saying that one tans with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$b~","text_ar":"شبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", this word is a mistranscription; for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$b~","text_ar":"شبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a dye, and one does not tan with a dye; it is mistranscribed for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$av~","text_ar":"شَثّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is a kind of tree like the dwarf apple-tree, whereof the leaves are like those of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xilaAf","text_ar":"خِلَاف"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.], and with them one tans: El-Fárábee also says, in the section of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"v","text_ar":"ث"},{"kind":"text","text":", that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$av~","text_ar":"شَثّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a species of mountain-tree, with which one tans: from all which it appears that one tans with both of them; for an affirmation is to be preferred to a negation: (Msb:) and it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a well-known medicine;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) as some say: so accord. to the correct copies of the K, in some of which,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daA='N","text_ar":"دَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dawaA='N","text_ar":"دَوَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","S","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n21526","headword_ar":"شُبّ","root":"$b","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dub~","text_ar":"دُبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", though originally verbs, are used as nouns, by the introduction of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino","text_ar":"مِنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"before them: one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoyayotaniY mino $ub~a A_ilaY dub~a","text_ar":"اَعْيَيْتَنِى مِنْ شُبَّ اـِلَى دُبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino $ub~K","text_ar":"مِنْ شُبٍّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY dub~K","text_ar":"اـِلَى دُبٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[expl. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dba","text_ar":"دبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:) and in like manner they are used in another saying expl. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"db","text_ar":"دب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: (S in that art.:) or, without tenween, they may be regarded as verbs used in the way of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HikaAyap","text_ar":"حِكَايَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or imitation]. (MF.)"}],"source_refs":["S"]}]}}